\\var is variable declaration without limitation of any scope. const is a variable which has a fixed value and can't be changed lateer
\\let is variable declaration within a scope only. var declare value without any limitation. let is newer declaration if compared to var
\\let allow multiple value to be assigned to a variable, given to the latest order. const allow only one value to be assigned to the variable.
\\let bring more confidence to code, use within a scope, var is use within a small project, one developer is there to maintain, const is a fixed value variable or variable when developer is not sure of what value to assign
